VAIFORM — ROUTES / APP / MOUNT RULES

Applies to:
- src/app.js
- server.js
- src/routes/**

Rules:
- src/app.js is the runtime mount authority.
- Preserve /api-first posture.
- Do not add new root aliases or dual mounts.
- Do not mount product functionality outside /api/*.
- Respect debug gating and internal-only route posture.
- Any route/mount change must be verified against:
  - docs/MAINTENANCE_FRONT_DOOR.md
  - docs/DOCS_INDEX.md
  - docs/API_CONTRACT.md
  - relevant scope docs
- If route truth changes materially, update the owning canonical docs first, then any needed evidence docs.
- Do not infer route truth from exports alone; confirm actual mounts in src/app.js.
